[[size 150%]]-- 2022 --[[/size]]
[[/=]]
------
@@ @@


[[div class="seers_memo4"]]

[[span style="color:white"]]
[[<]]
The following is a decree of compromise and friendship, by the mercy and grace of his imperial majesty tsar Alexander, Emperor and Autocrat of all Russia, and on behalf of his Seers, between the Domovoy tribes of the land of Ibeiqia on the continent of Aderon and the Russian Empire. 

In exchange for recognition of the colony of New Yekaterinburg by local gnomish kingdoms, Russia agrees not to expand nor engage in any resource collection or construction efforts north of the Gorchakov Line lying 1,095 kilometers north of Port Golovnin extending to the edge of the Ibeiqia Peninsula. The Russian Outer Ring Exploratory Company has already been alerted of and assented to these proceedings. May this executive exercise of his majesty's great kindness and magnanimity be effective beginning immediately on this day, the 9th of December, 1870.
[[/<]]
[[/span]]

[[/div]]


[[div class="journal"]]
**October 24th, 2022.**
The wild Domovoy of the First Ring suffered a much more tragic fate than those who settled as household spirits in the Known World. In Ibeiqia, where they once lived at peace under the canopies and carved out homes from the giant mushrooms, the successive thaumic chaos of the deicide and the Sealing cast a malignant undeath over their forest home.
@@ @@
The fungi are now the overlords of these forest-dwelling gnomes, what remains of their homes and shops and town squares overgrown with rotting biomass and their shambling corpses animated only by roots of mycelium to further spread the spores of contagion. Ex-Russian colonial cities were abandoned when the Veil began, allowing the epidemic to spread to them as well. Now the streets I walk are empty and filled with the stench of decay, the only few survivors having fled to the deepest caves or the tops of the highest trees. 
@@ @@
I am fortunate to have not been consumed by the infection outright upon discovering it when I arrived at the shores of Ibeiqia, for the fungal plague only feeds upon the already-deceased. I have taken enough notes and harvested enough samples; now I must leave to make sure I don't join their ranks.
[[/div]]


@@ @@
[[=image https://lounge.hexick.com/uploads/0a423dea78e5984d/image.png style="width: 50px;"]]
[[=]]
[[size 200%]]Grand Telug[[/size]]
[[size 150%]]-- 2022 --[[/size]]
[[/=]]
------
@@ @@

[[div style="border:solid 2px #004F00; background:#f2f2c2; padding:5px; margin-bottom: 5px;"]]

[[=]]
[[size 130%]] //**Of the Mountebanks**// [[/size]]
[[/=]]

[[div style="overflow:auto"]]

[[div style="display: inline-block; border:solid 1px #004F00; background:#FFFDD9; padding: 5px; float: left; margin-bottom: 5px; width: 260px; min-height: 100px;"]]
[[size 90%]]//Wander Library halls in trepidation,
For no page turned escapes the reach of those fiends who lurk between the words,
They slink and crawl across the halls and look for souls in desperation,
Sing songs of the fantastic, and of the absurd,
Tricks and cons age-old still fool ambitious men,
And so their foolhardy souls a Mountebank rends.//[[/size]]
[[/div]]

[[div style="border: solid 1px #004F00; background:#FFFDD9; padding:5px; margin: 0 0 5px 280px; min-height: 250px;"]]
The Mountebanks are an infernal consortium based in the lands of Telug^^1^^ and Tiran on the continent of Veipera in the Second Ring. Their influence can be felt across the whole of Earth, from the kingdoms, city-states and principalities of Europe and Isea, to the vast expanses of the Asian steppe and the Pleostrian wilds, to the wilds of Yazoya, Australia, Australis, and Sahul, as well as in much of the Library. The Mountebanks offer demonic bargains on a scale and with a level of syndicated coordination unheard of for any organization of terrestrial fiend-bloods, particularly considering such mortals must divinatively locate and translocate to their targets manually without the privileges of tartarean planarity. Those among their ranks will often wash up in the Library bearing great tales -- often, but not always fabricated -- of past deeds and bargains made, not to mention silver-tongued promises of what could be offered to a prospective wanderer, aiming to swindle them into a favorable deal.

The home of the Mountebanks is a desolate territory inland with only a few coastal cities, where sulfuric mountains are mined for brimstone and mercury as demons emerge from their calderas and settle by the blackened sea. It is said those who pawn their spirits to the Mountebanks are reborn in one of the combusting mountains as a fiend of Tartarus themselves, being forced to work in their new unlife for the native entities in their hives and elsewhere in their ashen homeland.

[[/div]]

-----

[[div style="border:solid 1px #004F00; background:#FFFDD9; padding: 5px; margin-bottom: 3px;"]]
//"The shaitan defrauders arrived in my court carrying all manner of treasures and unholy splendor from their forsaken bargains. One representative presented a crystal globe within which the stars were visible with total clarity; the other had a pair of goggles he claimed could allow one to see the auras of Thaum. Had I not been warned in advance, I am ashamed to admit I may have fallen for these trinkets."// â€” Fourth Sultan of Iinkiltira
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

^^1: Variably known also as Teluq, Teluc, or Teliq in the languages of the Veiperan lizardfolk.^^
[[/div]]

@@ @@

[[div class="journal"]]
**October 22nd, 2022.**
@@ @@
I'm only stopping briefly at a port with pre-existing thaumic shielding and air purification, since humans can hardly breathe here if exposed, the air polluted with sulfur and ash and the brimstone mountains that litter the landscape inland. The only documentation of Telug I have access to is a clipping from a tome of a Serpent's Hand precursor organization from around the time of the Sealing, describing it as the operating base of a mercurial and potentially-threatening Group of Interest with often multiversal reach -- I had never heard of the so-called Mountebanks, but notes appended by Extradimensional Relations apparently indicate they're still out and about, a major thorn in our side to this day.
@@ @@
If this source is to be believed, the Brimstone Hills of the Second Ring haven't changed much in the past hundred-odd years. The Sealing, as intended, saw a considerable drop in tartarean contact with mortals in the Prime Earth, but if the wanderers are to be believed, they could have made up for it by continuing their forays into the Library and scattering across the Ways for new targets. In any event, we're probably seeing one of the longest-standing continuous civilizations in Greater Earth still going strong, and nobody on our side of the Sealing Bound -- not the Foundation or the GOC or any equivalent body -- has even bothered to check up on them or the threat they pose.
@@ @@
We've been to the stars and back since 1881, but I'm beginning to realize how much we neglected the potential threats on our own doorstep in that time by insisting to lock them out and us from them both ways. In many cases, occult continents and civilizations in outlying dimensionalities of our own world were and remain more distant and obscure than any distant planet or star. All the Sealing did was exaggerate this; the Foundation has bases on the Moon and on Mars, but not one in even the First Ring, and that was intended by design when the Veil was signed into existence. And in those places we abandoned and overlooked, there were already empires as vast in scale as China or as dynamic and commercially-influential as Britain or France. //That// was in 1881 -- how advanced are they now? If you look between the creases and the folds of old mages' maps, once in a blue moon you'll see things that would be a security threat greater than anything or anyone terrestrial the Foundation deals with; They could still be out and at large today, and we would have no way of knowing.
[[/div]]

@@ @@
[[=image https://lounge.hexick.com/uploads/0a423dea78e5984d/image.png style="width: 50px;"]]
[[=]]
[[size 200%]]Bermuda Ultima[[/size]]
[[size 150%]]-- 2022 --[[/size]]
[[/=]]
------
@@ @@

[[div class="terminal"]]
[[div class="scanline"]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="text"]]
+ [[size 160%]]##80FF80|CCRU##[[/size]]

The hyperstitional parageographic exclave now known as Bermuda Ultima was discovered by polymath Daniel Charles Barker on an expedition intended to uncover archaeological remnants of Lemurian temporal eigenweapons in 1977. The unique feature of this location is an unintentionally-created hypersigil spanning the entire land area of the island, causing the patagenetic insertion of narrative devices representing anomalous persons, objects, and phenomena. All manifestations that appear in Bermuda Ultima are concepts obscured via fictionalization by the SCP Foundation, a massively-accelerative spectacular Cold God entity sovereign over the majority of physical paranormal reality. This leads to a critical mass of the "Prime" human population believing said concept to be fictitious, such as is sufficient to hypersigil contribution and hyperstitious construction in the form of mythogenesis.
@@ @@
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

@@ @@

[[div class="journal"]]
**October 30th, 2022.**
@@ @@
Today, I watched a triffid ride a pterosaur-dragon of Pellucidar between two floating rocks upon which stood hollow reflections of Shangri-La and Miskatonic University. I saw Mongolian deathworms devour Nemo's Nautilus from the inside, and disembowel a thousand shadow-clones of Oberon and Gloriana a thousand times over.
@@ @@
I can //try// to explain.
@@ @@
Most of the occult world wanes in magic when the Foundation exerts its will. This island in the Second Ring -- many call it Bermuda Ultima -- is among the only ones which responded to the post-Sealing world with a massive flare of newfound anomalous activity. Before the Sealing, it was by all accounts a mundane island; if it existed at all, nobody had heard of it or bothered to record its location in any detail. But after the instantiation of that ritual, and more pressingly of [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-6460/offset/2 Project Pantheon], massive noetic shifts in Prime caused the paranormal waste products of the Veil to be dumped here and fueled a dormant narrative anomaly, giving rise to a new land where all the fictions and false truths spread by the perpetuation of normalcy become real.
@@ @@
Never before has such an event been recorded by Foundation pataphysicians or misinformation noetics specialists to my best knowledge. Regardless of where the Veil led the Prime World, those it left behind certainly found a home elsewhere within their new status of irreality.
[[/div]]


