[[=]]
[[size 200%]]Unknown Hyperway[[/size]]
[[size 120%]]Beneath Jerusalem, Prime Earth[[/size]]
[[size 150%]]-- January 2023 --[[/size]]
[[/=]]
------
@@ @@

[[div class="jotting"]]

++ Telegraph Transmission 4/4/1878

Fritz.

Discovered something massive. Urgently require a consensus from you and Sophia before I go in. Get on the first train to Jerusalem.

Aaron.
[[/div]]

@@ @@

[[div class="journal"]]
**January 2nd, 2023.**
@@ @@
My next stop was supposed to be a trading port on an 18th-century alchemist's map, believed to be somewhere in the Opal Sea. Suffice it to say, this is not that port. The Hyperways did not function as I expected them to, and I have no idea where I have been taken.
@@ @@
I believe I've found myself in some liminal realm sprung from Hyperway malfunctions after the Sealing, or from some other thaumic disturbance, though I know not what could be happening currently in that capacity. I see winding halls on the other side of a great wall of Not; a curtain of some invisible substance viscous and static but nevertheless permeable when I put through my hand slow enough. Perhaps a portal of some kind?
@@ @@
I see two people on the other side. A man and a woman in some sort of underground room. Perhaps I'll try to step through.
[[/div]]

